# GNU Stow local ignore file.
#
# Read by `stow --dotfiles` (see stow_setup.sh) when symlinking the
# repo into $HOME. Anything matching a pattern here is NOT symlinked.
#
# Structure mirrors the root .gitignore: blanket deny at the top,
# narrow/allowlist-style comments below that single out the things
# this repo's stow should specifically skip.
#
# Stow itself only supports deny patterns (no allowlist), so this
# is a documentation-as-code convention — keep it complete. If you
# add a new top-level dotfile (e.g. `.foo.toml`), add it to the
# "Dev infrastructure" section below.

# ── Repo meta (not for ~) ─────────────────────────────────
README.md
LICENSE
assets

# ── Repo internals (not for ~) ────────────────────────────
.git
.claude

# ── Dev infrastructure (linter, formatter, CI configs) ────
# These live in the repo so the lint stack is reproducible, but
# they must NOT pollute $HOME — stow would symlink them as plain
# dotfiles and tools would pick them up unexpectedly.
#
# If you add a new tool config at the repo root, add it here.
.pre-commit-config.yaml
.pre-push-config.yaml
.gitleaks.toml
.gitleaks-baseline.json
.shellcheckrc
.shfmt.toml
.prettierrc.json
.prettierignore
.markdownlint.yaml
.markdownlint-cli2.yaml
pyproject.toml
.ruff.toml
.editorconfig
.github
.gitlab-ci.yml
.circleci

# ── Setup / bootstrap scripts (run from the repo, not from ~)
full_setup.sh
stow_setup.sh
required_packages_archlinux.txt

# ── Notes & vendor blobs (not for ~) ──────────────────────
_extra_notes
_spicetify_theme_configs
